  <section class="about">
    <div style="width: 160px; margin: 0 auto 20px;">
      <%= image_tag "challenge.png", width: "100%" %>
    </div>
    <p class="copy_desc english">Fireworks festivals are an integral part of the Japanese summer. Every day of this season, many are taking place, all over the country. Nowadays, though, everyone watches the fireworks through their smartphones. This is no how these festivals were meant to be enjoyed. For these people, imprisoned behind their degital screens, we are offering the chance of freedom.</p>
    <div style="width: 400px; margin: 30px auto;">
      <%= image_tag "challenge2.png", style: " width: 100%; margin: 0 auto;" %>
    </div>
    <div style="width: 160px; margin: 0 auto 20px;">
      <%= image_tag "solution.png", width: "100%" %>
    </div>
    <p class="copy_desc english">A special web app service that allows you to take home these impressive moments without missing the real thing. Simply tap the screen at your favourite points, and a photo of the fireworks at this exact moment will be sent to your smartphones. After the event you can browse at your leisure through high quality photographs taken from various different angles. Furthermore, the total number of taps from all the festival goers are plotted onto one graph, so at just a glance you can see the overall most popular and exciting moments of the whole festival.</p>
